        </div>

        <br>
        &nbsp;
        <br>
        <div style="font-size: 15px;">
            <h3 id="location">
                Location
            </h3>
            <br>
            One of the greatest deciding factors when choosing a gym or leisure center is its location.
            <br>
            Using our gyms near me gym locator this should make things easy.
            The next step would be too look at the types of membership/contract the gym are offering.
        </div>
        <br>
        &nbsp;
        <br>

        <h3 id="membership">
            Membership Type
        </h3>
        <br>
        <div style="font-size: 15px;">
            Most gyms offer a range of membership types, specifically leisure centers.
            <br>
            These can range from a year long one time payment contract, to monthly payments to one off day/week passes.
            <br>
            Before committing to a membership be sure to know its terms and conditions inside and out.
            <br>
            The most important parts to understand are:
            <br>
            <br>
            <div style="color: red; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold">
            Contract Length.
                <br>
                One off joining fees.
                <br>
                Whats included in the membership.
            <br>
            Any additional costs.             <br>
                Guest fee (bring a friend).             <br>
                Ability to freeze membership.
            <br>
            Non-peak hour contracts.             <br>
                Opening and closing times.
            </div>
            <br>
            <br>
            Our gym locator and gym comparison apps can help quickly distinguish these differences between gyms.
            <br>
            But be sure to always check the gym yourself as additional updates and changes may have been made.
            <br>
            Some gyms will also offer specific packages to students, 60+, teenagers, disability or one of tokens.

        </div>
        <br>
        &nbsp;
        <br>

        <h3 id="coronavirus">
            Coronavirus Restrictions
        </h3>
        <br>
        <div style="font-size: 15px;">
            Many gyms have recently undergone reforms to ensure they meet government coronavirus standards.
            <br>
            This means gyms may have limited the number of people inside the gym at once, cut down on hours, or shut down facilities.
            <br>
            There may also be other specific rules as well such as wearing a mask / bringing gloves - make sure you find out about these.
        </div>
        <br>
        &nbsp;
        <br>

        <h3 id="equipment">
            Gym Equipment & Facilities
        </h3>
        <br>
        <div style="font-size: 15px;">
            Know what you are looking for in a gym/facility before signing upto one.
            <br>
            Some gyms offer only cardio, some offer just weights, some offer swim,ing pools and sauna rooms ect. Some offer all of these.
            <br>
            If any of these are important to your needs, see if they are available.
        </div>
        <br>
        &nbsp;
        <br>

        <h3 id="classes">
            Gym classes & Personal Trainers
        </h3>
        <br>
        <div style="font-size: 15px;">
            Have a look into gym classes, personal trainers, prices and the impacts of Coronavirus on these services if interested in them.
            <br>
            Some classes may be free and turn-up, whereas others may be pre-book and pay.
            <br>
            Having a training plan / programme can be extremely beneficial and may teach you alot - but its important to know whats available beforehand.
        </div>
